  "text": "With the exception of the Ethiopian Jews, all the populations have been previously analyzed for subsets of the Y-chromosome polymorphisms used in the present study (see references in table 1). Slight differences between these studies and the present work in sample sizes for some populations reflect subsequent unavailability of DNA. Mbuti and Biaka Pygmies and the small Lissongo sample were previously reported as \"central Africa\" in the article by [CITATION_1] . Several subjects from Europe (63 Spanish, 20 Italians, 15 Danes, and 4 Poles), and eight subjects from the Middle East have been also analyzed for a specific mutation (M269) and were included for comparison with the African data (see the \"Geographic Distribution of Haplotypes\" subsection of the \"Results\" section).",
